# Release Checklist for CardCast

## Pre-Release Testing

### Functionality Tests
- [ ] Pokemon card search works
- [ ] OBS overlays display correctly
- [ ] Deck import/export functions
- [ ] Download progress shows properly
- [ ] Socket.io real-time updates work
- [ ] Database operations (CRUD) work
- [ ] Error handling displays user-friendly messages

### Build Tests
- [ ] `npm test` passes
- [ ] `npm run build` creates dist-portable successfully
- [ ] CardCast.bat launches correctly
- [ ] Auto-downloads Node.js if not installed
- [ ] Dependencies install on first run
- [ ] Server starts and opens browser

### Cross-System Tests
- [ ] Windows 10 compatibility
- [ ] Windows 11 compatibility
- [ ] Works with Node.js 16+
- [ ] Works with Node.js 18+
- [ ] Works with Node.js 20+

## Release Preparation

### Code Updates
- [ ] Version number updated in package.json
- [ ] CHANGELOG.md updated with new version
- [ ] README.md reviewed and updated
- [ ] Config.json has correct defaults
- [ ] Remove any debug console.log statements
- [ ] Remove any test data

### Documentation
- [ ] README.md is current
- [ ] CHANGELOG.md has release date
- [ ] API documentation is updated
- [ ] OBS setup guide is clear
- [ ] Troubleshooting section covers known issues

### Build Process
```bash
# Clean build
npm run clean
npm install
npm test
npm run build
```

### Distribution Package
- [ ] Build creates dist-portable/ folder
- [ ] All required files are included:
  - [ ] CardCast.bat
  - [ ] server.js
  - [ ] package.json
  - [ ] config.json
  - [ ] index.html
  - [ ] src/ folder
  - [ ] public/ folder
  - [ ] overlays/ folder
  - [ ] scripts/ folder
  - [ ] README.txt
- [ ] Test the distribution on clean system
- [ ] ZIP file size is reasonable (<15MB)

## GitHub Release

### Create Release
1. Tag version: `git tag v1.0.0`
2. Push tag: `git push origin v1.0.0`
3. Create GitHub release
4. Title: `CardCast v1.0.0 - Pokemon TCG Support`
5. Attach `CardCast-v1.0.0-portable.zip`

### Release Notes Template
```markdown
## CardCast v1.0.0

### Features
- Full Pokemon TCG support (20,000+ cards)
- Real-time OBS overlays
- Offline mode after initial download
- Deck import/export
- Auto-updating card data

### Installation
1. Download CardCast-v1.0.0-portable.zip
2. Extract to any folder
3. Run CardCast.bat
4. Follow setup instructions

### Requirements
- Windows 10 or later
- 2GB free disk space
- Internet for initial card download

### What's New
- [List major changes]

### Known Issues
- [List any known problems]

### Coming Soon
- Magic: The Gathering support
- Yu-Gi-Oh! support
- More overlay designs

Full changelog: [CHANGELOG.md]
```

## Post-Release

### Community
- [ ] Announce on Reddit (r/Twitch, r/obs, r/pkmntcg)
- [ ] Post on Twitter/X
- [ ] Share in Discord communities
- [ ] Update project website (if exists)

### Monitoring
- [ ] Watch GitHub issues for bug reports
- [ ] Monitor download statistics
- [ ] Gather user feedback
- [ ] Plan next version features

### Backup
- [ ] Tag release in Git
- [ ] Backup distribution file
- [ ] Archive release notes
- [ ] Document any hotfix procedures

## Hotfix Procedure

If critical bug found:
1. Fix in `hotfix/v1.0.1` branch
2. Test thoroughly
3. Update version to 1.0.1
4. Rebuild and test distribution
5. Create new release
6. Notify users of update

## Version Numbering

- **Major** (1.0.0): New TCG support or breaking changes
- **Minor** (1.1.0): New features, overlay designs
- **Patch** (1.0.1): Bug fixes, small improvements

---

Remember: Quality over speed. Test thoroughly before release!